# Shared Dev Server

Only one terminal instance should run the project dev servers at a time.

Before starting any frontend, backend, watcher, or combined dev server:

- Check the existing IDE terminals for an already-running dev server.
- Reuse the existing dev server terminal when it is healthy.
- Do not start a duplicate dev server in a new terminal just because this agent is working in parallel with other agents.
- If the existing dev server is unhealthy or needs a restart, stop or restart that same terminal process instead of creating a second long-running instance.
- If a separate server is truly required, explain why before starting it.

This applies to both the backend server and the frontend dev server.
